Results.ReviewText: For many years I've used Gold Blend.  Then I discovered NESCAFÉ Gold Blend Crema.  This is the most delicious instant coffee I have ever bought, and I have  over 40 years 'experience' of drinking coffee, different brands and different products.  Yes it is as described.... smooth, rounded and creamy.  But better than that it IS the best coffee to use in team tea kittys or for company guests and clients.  Why?  because it is a quality drink, far superior to ordinary Gold Blend.  Looks good when served with a distinctive 'top', has a rich coffee taste but without  sharpness.  This is the only coffee that I've served to company guests and clients that is universally finished to the last drop.   Now that says something.
Results.Title: Delicious - best all round choice.

Results.ReviewText: My cupboard is full of Nescafe products, Azeera Americans for everyday, Expression for my other half and for treats and after dinner.....Crema!!!!  This instant coffee is, as are they all, everything it promises to be.  It is rich, very smooth but tasty.  It is like liquid velvet.  I hate coffee which has no flavour but this is a real taste experience!!!  Every evening, after dinner, when the chores are complete, this coffee is my secret vice.  It makes me feel good and I love it!!!!  It is for special guests only as I love it too much to share but, those chosen ones I have converted!!!!  Never stop making this Nescafe!!!!  It really is the dog's wotsits!!!!!!
Results.Title: Sheer Decadence In A Jar

Results.ReviewText: I bought a jar of Nescafe Gold Crema around 5/6 weeks ago.  The coffee has a distinctive, smooth, light and creamy taste.  It isn't as strong as other coffee brands that i've tasted, which was an added bonus.  The value of the coffee was quite good, when I compare it to other brands I have tried.  A friend came over to visit and I made her a cup of this coffee.  She commented on how nice it tasted, said she had never heard of it or tried it before and then said she'd be going out to buy a jar of it.  In general people never comment on coffee, but this made a lasting impression.  I doubt I'd go back to another brand/type of coffee now I've tried it.  It is excellent, in my opinion.
Results.Title: Nescafe Gold Crema

Results.ReviewText: I bought this as an alternative to my normal Nescafe a few weeks ago and I'm so glad I tried it. I love the velvety taste of this coffee, which isn't bitter, just smooth and rich in taste. We don't drink a lot of coffee at home, but like a good quality instant coffee and this ticks all the boxes. I warm the milk first, add the Crema and a sugar to taste, then pour on boiling water, stirring all the while. It has a lovely rich aroma that makes my taste buds tingle and for the price, it's an excellent cup of coffee. If you like a smooth, creamy coffee without paying premium prices, you should try this!
Results.Title: Deliciously creamy!

Results.ReviewText: I had the pleasure of consuming this new coffee yesterday. I haven't been allowed caffeine for over a year, so this really hit the spot! The crema was fantastic, I couldn't believe this was an instant coffee! I'm looking forward to enjoying this on the balcony every morning.
Results.Title: Delicious taste! Can't wait to keep drinking it :)

ClientResponses.Response: Hi, thanks for getting in touch! We've made changes to our NESCAFÉ Gold coffee but there's been no change to NESCAFÉ Gold Crema. If you want us to check this out for you please call us on: 0800 58 57 59. Your reference number to quote is:11477626

Results.ReviewText: I buy two jars of this coffee every month, so 24 a year on average. I don't know what you have done to it but it has recently changed and all of the rich flavour is gone. The same thing has happened to Nescafe Gold. So now I have no choice but to find another instant coffee provider, which has actually made me angry as I love, love, love Crema - well I did...
Results.Title: Another one they have ruined!

Results.ReviewText: I love this coffee, it is rich,  flavourful, deep and just so moreish. Theres no bitter aftertaste and the silky smoothness of it even appealed to my daughter who isnt a coffee drinker. A lovely 'anytime' drink.
Results.Title: Decadent

Results.ReviewText: I started to use Crema years ago and although I have since tried other coffees ( including expensive Colombian ones ) nothing comes close in terms of smoothness and feeling of luxury. The ingredients show that it is only coffee but the result is an outstanding drink that is way above the others for taste and satisfaction.
Results.Title: Crema - how do they do it ?

Results.ReviewText: We bought this today, we thought crema meant it had cream or milk in it probably in powder form. Nothing on label description to say what it is or what crema means.
Results.Title: What'in time? What does 'crema' mean?

Results.ReviewText: After being pregnant and off coffee for nine months, I am so pleased to come back to a coffee like this!  I love the smooth and creamy taste of this coffee.  It is not too bold and intense flavour, rather it is a smooth and refreshing taste.  Perfect for a relaxing start to the day - and a great pick me up in the afternoon without being a too sharp hit of coffee.  I don't normally have my coffee black but I find that I don't mind this coffee with or without milk, and it is a nice change to be able to find a coffee that I'm able to enjoy without milk.
Results.Title: Perfect Start to the Day

Results.ReviewText: Thought I'd give this a try - love the old Nescafe Gold but so did my fellow coffee drinkers and the volume level in the jar disappeared just that little bit too quickly!!! Now I don't need to mess around remembering to take milk into work because Cream Gold is rich enough to enjoy but with a rich creamy layer to satisfy my sweeter side. So I enjoy my coffee more - it stays in my drawer and my peers buy their own. Result!  I can thoroughly recommend Nescafe Gold Crema to them, but think they might just prefer the other options and add their own milk.
Results.Title: At last my Office coffe is safe!

Results.ReviewText: Bought this as was looking for a smoother tasting instant coffee to use with my milk frother Nescafe Gold Crema fits the bill perfectly. I'm not a fan of coffee machines as the coffee pods are too expensive but I love coffee so using Nescafe Gold Crema in warm frothy milk makes the most perfect Latte without the cost of coffee pods or coffee shops. Perfection in a jar!
Results.Title: Perfection in a jar

Results.ReviewText:
I love this coffee do much. It is so smooth and creamy. The smell is not a strong pungent one like regular ground coffee can be and welcomes you and says 'hey lets have coffee'
Would highly recommend it. 
The only downside is that I cant get it in a large 1kg tub because it can be a bit more pricey and we all have money to save.
Results.Title: The best

Results.ReviewText: I went off the original gold blend and looked around for another coffee, this Crema is one smooth cup of coffee and I prefer it to say Azera Americano which is so similar but not as smooth. I stress smooth over strong. I drink it black so I think this makes a difference.
Results.Title: my favourite coffee for a while now.

Results.ReviewText: For a coffee blend that I have not tried before, this was a wonderfully smooth delight to consume. Creamy, flavorsome and with just the right blend of flavors. I lost myself in the taste of this wonderful product. A sheer delight
Results.Title: Supreme Crema!

Results.ReviewText: I was looking forward to trying this and wasn't disappointed. The velvety sensation engaged with my taste buds to make for a successfully flavoursome experience.
Results.Title: A successfully flavoursome experience!

ClientResponses.Response: It's sad to hear you're not a fan but thank you for letting us know!

Results.ReviewText: Bought a jar, it tastes very watery and bitter! Tried with more coffee and hot milk, not at all worth the money.  Sorry Nescafe you got this very wrong!!
Results.Title: Tastes very weak

Results.ReviewText: I bought this thinking it would suit my husband and be too strong for me as strong coffee invariably gives me indigestion. How wrong I was ! It is smooth, easy to drink and no after effects at all! I know a lot of over 50's suffer with reflux and indigestion and it can be debilitating. I really missed my morning cup of coffee for a long time. Not any more my nescafe crema is a godsend. The taste is divine and the crema top well just wow. As good as any Italian restaurant!
Results.Title: Smooooth

Results.ReviewText: I like my lattes with a nice creamy top, so thought i would try this nescafe coffee to see if it comes close, and boy was i pleasantly surprised.  The first taste of this coffee made me totally forget about shop bought creamy coffees.  Such a velvety smooth taste of a typical nescafe taste, added with a lovely creamy topping made it the perfect breakfast - on the go coffee.  I even found myself taking a coffee to work in a flask to enjoy it in the brisk outdoors.
Results.Title: Smooth, Crisp and Amazingly Tasty

ClientResponses.Response: Hi, thanks very much for letting us know your thoughts on the new recipe. Although it's sad to hear you're unhappy with the changes we've made, we really appreciate your feedback! The residue you can see at the bottom of your cup is micro ground coffee that was added to NESCAFÉ Gold Blend during the recent change. This is non-soluble coffee and gives you a similar experience to that of a barista made coffee! We've made a note of your comments & will be passing them to the rest of the team!

Results.ReviewText: I bought two jars of this product a few weeks ago and I am half way through the first jar. I went to my local Morrisons today to ask if they would refund my money because I am so disappointed in the product. I have been a Gold Blend drinker for many years but this coffee is unpleasant as it leaves  dusty residue in the bottom of the cup. Morrisons told me that I should contact Nescafé direct. Can you please give this complaint your attention.
Results.Title: Not great

Results.ReviewText: Saw it on offer and thought why not, i use the 2 in 1 nescafe sachets every day for work and love them but this crema instant is even more creamy and delicious. It feels like a real treat and bit of luxury. Several friends and relatives have now gone out and bought it as a result of trying it at mine. wonderful, I even took some in a small tupperware when we went to a hotel in the lake district recently.
Results.Title: deliciously luxurious a real treat

Results.ReviewText:
I wasn't going to buy this coffee as I am a confirmed Nescafe Granules drinker. I am however, so glad that I did. It reminded me of the coffee of long ago. With a super rich smell and a taste you would expect from Nescafe how could I go wrong.
After making the coffee, and my husband drinking half of it, I made another.
So rich, so smooth and everything I wanted in a cup of 'homemade' coffee.
Results.Title: Proper Coffee

Results.ReviewText: I have been using this coffee since I first saw it on sale, I much prefer my coffee in powder form not granules and this is probably the best tasting coffee I have tried, please don't change it as I was using your instant cappuccino's until you changed the ingredients which made them unpalatable for me and I don't want to go back to trying lots of different coffees again.
Results.Title: great instant coffee

Results.ReviewText: This was sitting at the work kitchen. Curiosity killed the cat on this one. Rich and smooth taste. with that first sip, Swirling it around your mouth first thing in the morning just saying "mmmm life is good ". With the kick of caffeine you are ready to attack your day. overall tastes very authentic and unique. As a Colombian i know my coffee very well.
Results.Title: rich and smooth

Results.ReviewText: I am a big coffee drinker and tried all the instants available over the years.  I've been drinking Nescafe Crema from it's outset and not changed brands since.  I love the smoothness of flavour and particularly love the golden crema formed after adding hot water.  It looks amazing.  This is most definitely the best instant coffee on the market for me.
Results.Title: Sophisticated brew

Results.ReviewText: I have been using Nescafe for years and it has always delivered great quality instant coffee. My cupboard always has Nescafe and it is my go-to brand for a good cup of instant coffee. This Crema blend is another great addition to the family. I love the creamy texture and smooth velvety taste. It's indulging, smooth and delicious!
Results.Title: Always delivers

Results.ReviewText: I love the taste of this coffee, especially first thing in the morning. It sets me up for the day. It's so easily prepared and yet I prefer it's smooth yet rich aroma to filter coffee, whether I drink it black, white or with flavouring. A fantastic all rounder which can always be found in my kitchen! Couldn't be without it!
Results.Title: My preferred coffee

Results.ReviewText: After trying so many different brands and remaining quite disappointed in seeking out the perfect instant coffee I turned to Nescafe Gold to try out the Crema and instantly found it so smooth and creamy that it blows all the others away. No harsh, aggressive flavour or bitter after taste, so it's Nescafe Crema from now on.
Results.Title: Smoother than silk

Results.ReviewText: I am very surprised with this product. I must admit I am not a fan of instant coffee but this one is amazing and proved me wrong! It is definitely worth your money as the taste is great and very smooth. If you want a quick great cup of delicate coffee this should be your first choice! Thanks Nescafe for proving me wrong!
Results.Title: lovely surprise

Results.ReviewText: I saw this while out food shopping and thought I would try it out as I do love my coffee!  I found it to very smooth, not at all grainy or bitter and the after taste was lovely and light, not too heavy at all, I really enjoyed this coffee and as a big fan of Nescafe products, I would definitely purchase in the future
Results.Title: Smooth and Satisfying!
